Hi All, I'm going through [Koan's Lazy Property example](https://play.kotlinlang.org/koans/Properties/Lazy%20property/Task.kt).

The question is

    Add a custom getter to make the val lazy really lazy. It should be initialized by invoking initializer() during the first access.
    You can add any additional properties as you need.
    Do not use delegated properties!

The answer is

    class LazyProperty(val initializer: () -&gt; Int) {
        var value: Int? = null
        val lazy: Int
            get() {
                if (value == null) {
                    value = initializer()
                }
                return value!!
            }
    }

I can also do it with

    class LazyProperty(val initializer: () -&gt; Int) {
        val lazy by lazy {
            initializer()
        }
    }

I'm not sure the intent of this tutorial introducing \`lazy\` by not using \`by lazy\`. Is it the intent of the tutorial to show us \`get()\` ?

